You are using the wrong dependency for jaxws for your purposes.  The difference in distributions is explained here:

 * https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5401358/whats-the-difference-between-jaxws-ri-and-jaxws-rt

`jaxws-ri` contains zipped documentation which should not be part of a modular distribution. 

These are [dependencies you should be using][1] (maven format, you will need to translate to gradle format):

    &lt;dependencies&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;jakarta.xml.ws&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;jakarta.xml.ws-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;4.0.0&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;

    &lt;dependencies&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;com.sun.xml.ws&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;jaxws-rt&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;4.0.0&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;runtime&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;

**Additional background info**

jaxws reference implementations are now maintained via the Eclipse foundation as jakarta XML services as part of [Eclipse Metro][2].  

The code should also use the `jakarta` package namespace as shown in the [jakarta documentation](https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/metro-jax-ws/4.0.0/docs/ch03.html).  

This would also apply to [module names][3] if you provide a module-info.


  [1]: https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/metro-jax-ws/
  [2]: https://github.com/eclipse-ee4j/metro-jax-ws
  [3]: https://jakarta.ee/specifications/xml-web-services/4.0/apidocs/jakarta.xml.ws/module-summary.html

